1.text: A Song of degrees of David.  Behold, how good and how pleasant it is for brethren to dwell together in unity!

2.text: It is like the precious ointment upon the head, that ran down upon the beard, even Aaron's beard: that went down to the skirts of his garments;

3.text: As the dew of Hermon, and as the dew that descended upon the mountains of Zion: for there the LORD commanded the blessing, even life for evermore.
